+# Per-parameter `mut` modifier flags (parallel to PARAM_NAMES; 1 = declared
+# `mut`, 0 = plain). #173: a `mut` struct param is the sanctioned "caller
+# observes the mutation" spelling, so 50.mir's #167 copy-on-param-bind must
+# be skipped for it -- previously the parser consumed and discarded the
+# modifier (parser_skip_mut_if_present). NOT stored via ast_decl_text_set:
+# that store silently drops any field outside its NAME/PARAM_NAMES/...
+# whitelist (see ast_decl_text_set above), so a dedicated idx-keyed side
+# table is used instead (same spirit as decl_is_value_type, dict-keyed so it
+# needs no arena push-alignment).
+var decl_param_muts_store: Dict<i64, text> = {}
